Four solid-state movable detectors were placed
inside the scattering chamber at intervals of 10 degr.
A fifth detector was placed at a fixed position for
* the accuracy of the charge integrator (0.8%);
* the error in the geometrical factor (3.5%);
* the errors in the temperature, pressure and charge.
The very small uncertainty in the measurement of the
angle of the detectors was neglected.
The statistical error is negligible for the elastic
scattering, while for (d,p) and (d,a0) reactions it
is of the order of a few per cent.
The statistical error flag is always smaller than
the dimensions of the points on the figures.
The 160 gas used as a target was approx. 99% pure.
The pressure of the gas in the scattering chamber was
regulated by differential pumping system.During the
